# Jira MCP Custom Fields — PR1050558 Project

When using the Atlassian MCP server (`plugin-atlassian-atlassian`) to fetch Jira issues for the **PR1050558** project, you MUST explicitly request the project's custom fields. The default `getJiraIssue` and `searchJiraIssuesUsingJql` responses only return standard fields and omit custom fields like Acceptance Criteria and Solution.

## Cloud ID

The Salesforce Jira cloud ID is: `e4adcd9e-7f5a-47eb-9e06-f34d025e104f`

## Required Custom Fields

Always include these in the `fields` array parameter:

| Display Name | Field ID | Type |
|---|---|---|
| Acceptance Criteria | `customfield_10033` | Rich text (ADF) |
| Solution | `customfield_10040` | Rich text (ADF) |
| Build Components | `customfield_10034` | Rich text (ADF) |
| Deployment Instructions | `customfield_10035` | Rich text (ADF) |
| Sprint | `customfield_10020` | Sprint array |
| Story Points | `customfield_10047` | Number |
| Percentage Complete | `customfield_10042` | Select |
| Business Owner | `customfield_10216` | User picker |
| Start Date | `customfield_10015` | Date |
| External ID | `customfield_10037` | Text |
| Date Confirmed | `customfield_10043` | Date |

## Standard `getJiraIssue` Call Template

When fetching a single story, always use this pattern:

```json
{
  "cloudId": "e4adcd9e-7f5a-47eb-9e06-f34d025e104f",
  "issueIdOrKey": "<STORY-KEY>",
  "fields": [
    "summary",
    "description",
    "status",
    "issuetype",
    "priority",
    "assignee",
    "components",
    "labels",
    "fixVersions",
    "parent",
    "issuelinks",
    "customfield_10033",
    "customfield_10040",
    "customfield_10034",
    "customfield_10035",
    "customfield_10020",
    "customfield_10047",
    "customfield_10042",
    "customfield_10216",
    "customfield_10015",
    "customfield_10037",
    "customfield_10043"
  ],
  "responseContentFormat": "markdown"
}
```

## Standard `searchJiraIssuesUsingJql` Call Template

When searching for stories, always include the same custom fields:

```json
{
  "cloudId": "e4adcd9e-7f5a-47eb-9e06-f34d025e104f",
  "jql": "<YOUR-JQL>",
  "fields": [
    "summary",
    "description",
    "status",
    "issuetype",
    "priority",
    "assignee",
    "components",
    "labels",
    "fixVersions",
    "customfield_10033",
    "customfield_10040",
    "customfield_10034",
    "customfield_10035",
    "customfield_10020",
    "customfield_10047",
    "customfield_10042"
  ],
  "responseContentFormat": "markdown"
}
```

## Content Format Notes

- Rich text custom fields (AC, Solution, Build Components, Deployment Instructions) are returned in **Atlassian Document Format (ADF)** — a nested JSON structure with `type: "doc"` at the root.
- Use `"responseContentFormat": "markdown"` to get the `description` field in markdown, but note that custom rich-text fields still come back as ADF regardless of this setting.
- When presenting AC or Solution content to the user, parse the ADF `content` array to extract the readable text, preserving structure (headings, lists, bold, links).

## Do NOT Rely on Defaults

Never call `getJiraIssue` without the `fields` parameter. The Jira REST API default "navigable" field set does NOT include project custom fields, which means **Acceptance Criteria, Solution, Build Components, and Deployment Instructions will be silently omitted**.
